---
/**
 * Terms & Conditions — dedicated page, linked separately in the footer and
 * below every form's consent checkboxes.
 *
 * The SMS section mirrors the consent language on the forms and the Privacy
 * Policy — all three read from business.ts, so they cannot contradict each
 * other. Contradictions between these three surfaces are a common rejection.
 *
 * NOTE: an honest starting set of terms that reflects how this business
 * actually operates. Not legal advice — have counsel review before launch.
 */
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageHero from '@components/PageHero.astro';
import { BUSINESS, addressOneLine, telHref, mailHref, serviceAreaLine } from '@data/business';

const LAST_UPDATED = 'July 16, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title={`Terms & Conditions | ${BUSINESS.legalName}`}
  description="The terms and conditions governing use of the Mateo Landscaping and More LLC website, our estimates and services, and our text messaging program."
  path="/terms-and-conditions"
>
  <PageHero eyebrow="Legal" title="Terms &amp; Conditions" crumb="Terms & Conditions" />

  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="prose-legal mx-auto max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-slate-soft)]">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

        <p>
          These Terms &amp; Conditions (“Terms”) govern your use of the website operated by{' '}
          <strong>{BUSINESS.legalName}</strong> (“we,” “us,” or “our”), and your participation in our
          text messaging program. By using this site or submitting a form, you agree to these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. About us</h2>
        <p>
          {BUSINESS.legalName} is a family-owned landscaping and home services company based at{' '}
          {addressOneLine}. We provide lawn care and landscaping, fencing, decks, and handyman and
          remodeling services. {serviceAreaLine}
        </p>

        <h2>2. Estimates and quotes</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Estimates are <strong>free and carry no obligation</strong>. Requesting one does not commit you to hiring us.</li>
          <li>
            Every property is different, so estimates are based on the specific work we assess on
            site. Information submitted through this website lets us prepare an estimate — it is not
            itself a binding quote.
          </li>
          <li>
            If conditions change once work begins — something hidden under the surface, an
            unforeseen obstruction, a change you request — we will discuss it with you and agree any
            price change <em>before</em> we carry out the extra work. You will not be surprised by an
            invoice.
          </li>
          <li>Estimates are valid for 30 days unless we state otherwise in writing.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Scheduling and access</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            We schedule in good faith and we show up when we say we will. Weather, ground conditions,
            and the pace of preceding jobs can move outdoor work; if that happens, we will contact you.
          </li>
          <li>
            You agree to provide safe, lawful access to the work area, and to tell us about anything
            we should know about — buried utilities, irrigation lines, invisible pet fencing, septic
            fields, easements, or property line disputes.
          </li>
          <li>
            You are responsible for obtaining any permission you need from a homeowners' association,
            landlord, or neighbour before work starts.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Permits, utilities and property lines</h2>
        <p>
          Some work — particularly fencing and decks — may require a permit or a utility locate. We
          will tell you when we believe one is needed, and we will not knowingly proceed without it.
          You are responsible for confirming your property boundaries. If a fence or structure is
          built on a line you identified and that line proves incorrect, the cost of relocating it is
          not covered by our warranty.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Payment</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Payment terms are set out in your estimate or invoice. Larger projects may require a deposit before materials are ordered.</li>
          <li>Invoices are due on the terms stated on the invoice.</li>
          <li>Materials remain our property until paid for in full.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Warranty</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>We stand behind our work.</strong> If our workmanship isn't right, tell us and we
          will come back and make it right. The specific warranty period and scope depend on the type
          of work and are stated in your estimate.
        </p>
        <p>Our warranty does not cover:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Damage from weather, storms, flooding, fire, or other events outside our control.</li>
          <li>Normal weathering, fading, seasonal movement, or the natural aging of wood and other materials.</li>
          <li>Damage caused by neglect, misuse, alteration, or work performed by someone else after we finish.</li>
          <li>
            Plant material beyond the establishment period stated in your estimate — living things
            depend on watering and care after we leave.
          </li>
          <li>Manufacturer defects in materials, which are covered by the manufacturer's own warranty. We will help you claim under it.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>7. Cancellation</h2>
        <p>
          Let us know as early as you can. If you cancel after we have ordered custom materials or
          begun work, you remain responsible for materials already purchased and work already
          performed. Where you have a cancellation right under Illinois or federal law, nothing in
          these Terms limits it.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Text messaging program</h2>
        <p>
          Our text messaging program is entirely optional. On our forms you may separately consent to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Transactional messages</strong> — reminders, appointment confirmations, and
            service updates relating to services you have requested from us; and
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Marketing and promotional messages</strong> — special offers, discounts, and
            seasonal service reminders.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Both consent boxes are unchecked by default and are optional. <strong>You are not required
          to consent to text messages in order to submit a form or to hire us</strong>, and consent to
          marketing messages is not a condition of any purchase.
        </p>
        <p>
          Message frequency may vary. Message and data rates may apply — those charges come from your
          mobile carrier, not from us. Reply <strong>HELP</strong> for help or <strong>STOP</strong>{' '}
          to opt out at any time. After you reply STOP we will send one confirmation message and then
          stop. Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our handling of your mobile information is described in our{' '}
          <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Use of this website</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The content, photographs, and design of this site are our property or are used under licence, and may not be copied for commercial use without our permission.</li>
          <li>You agree not to misuse the site, submit false information, or use our forms to send unsolicited or automated submissions.</li>
          <li>We may change or remove site content at any time.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Accuracy of information</h2>
        <p>
          We work to keep this site accurate and current, but we do not warrant that everything on it
          is complete or error-free. Photographs are illustrative of the type of work we do. Nothing
          on this website constitutes a binding offer or a guaranteed price.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by Illinois law, our total liability arising out of any job
          is limited to the amount you paid us for that job. We are not liable for indirect,
          incidental, or consequential damages. Nothing in these Terms excludes liability that cannot
          lawfully be excluded — including liability for death or personal injury caused by our
          negligence.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of {BUSINESS.homeStateFull}, without
          regard to its conflict of law rules. Any dispute will be brought in the state or federal
          courts located in {BUSINESS.homeStateFull}.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Changes to these Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. The version posted on this page at the time
          you use the site is the version that applies to you. Changes do not affect a contract we
          have already agreed with you.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Contact us</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>{BUSINESS.legalName}</strong></li>
          <li>{addressOneLine}</li>
          <li>Phone: <a href={telHref}>{BUSINESS.phoneDisplay}</a></li>
          <li>Email: <a href={mailHref}>{BUSINESS.email}</a></li>
        </ul>

        <hr class="rule-sand my-10" />
        <p class="text-sm text-[color:var(--color-slate-soft)]">
          &copy; {new Date().getFullYear()} {BUSINESS.legalName}. These Terms were last updated on{' '}
          {LAST_UPDATED}.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
